national FITNESS MONTH 
Ms. Jean Augustine ( Etobicoke - Lakeshore , Lib . ) : 
Mr. Speaker , May is National Fitness Month . 
may is a special month , the month of flowers , the month of good weather and the month in which we celebrate Mother ' s Day . 
yet , there are some among us who are seen as unreachable or as someone else ' s child . 
they are the sexually exploited youth who exist in a world of shadows invisible . 
the voice of these sexually exploited children and youth must be heard and strategies must be devised to meet their specific needs . 
a special program " Out from the shadows and into the light " was brought to my attention today . 
that special program is using a community development approach beginning with the youth themselves , the youth who tell their stories and the youth who make recommendations . 
i encourage all of my colleagues , as the Minister of Foreign Affairs has said , to express support for this program and to combat the sexual exploitation of children . 
